Title: From Being-Me to Being-We
---
When I lose myself in fear
and its other side, blame,

You tell me to take my
being-me and give it

to your being-You,
which is ever full of

unbecoming is-ness
and unnameable no-

thing-ness, so that
together we might

become a single
and simple being-we.
